@startuml
title zkSEC Control Architecture, Admissibility, and Route Checks

skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam component {
  FontSize 12
}
skinparam activity {
  FontSize 11
}

rectangle "CLI (cli.py)\nEntry: run()\nArgs: adapter, action, resource,\nrequest_payload, source, risk" as CLI
rectangle "Routing (routing.py)\nOutput: RoutedActionDecision" as ROUTER
rectangle "Admissibility (admissibility.py)\ntransform tuple\nZOS bridge\nunified detector\nattack harness" as ADMISSIBILITY
rectangle "Security (security.py)\nassess_action\nassess_data_boundary\npolicy_receipt" as SECURITY
rectangle "Adapter Contracts\n(contracts.py)\nzos_server | kant_zk_pastebin" as CONTRACTS
rectangle "Execution (execution.py)\nAdapterExecutionDirective" as EXECUTION
rectangle "Reporting (reporting.py)\nexecution_audit_record" as REPORTING
rectangle "Context/Sources (context.py)\nknown_adjacent_surfaces\ninvariants" as CONTEXT

node "policy preconditions\nreadiness gate" as PRECONDITION

CLI --> ROUTER : evaluate_adapter_action()
ROUTER --> SECURITY : assess_action()
ROUTER --> SECURITY : assess_data_boundary(action, resource, payload, resource_roots)
ROUTER --> CONTRACTS : _resolve_adapter()\nvalidate_action_against_adapter()
ROUTER --> ADMISSIBILITY : evaluate_transform_admissibility()\nbridge_zos_proposal()\nevaluate_unified_detector()
ROUTER --> PRECONDITION : policy_receipt\n(reason_code trail)

ROUTER --> CLI : RoutedActionDecision\nstatus = deny / requires_confirmation / allow\nreason_code
CLI --> EXECUTION : build_execution_directive(routed, operator, environment)
EXECUTION --> PRECONDITION : if status==allow\n  and action in {deploy,patch,remediate}\n  require actor_identity + scope + plan_ref\n  => execution_receipt_precondition_failed
EXECUTION --> REPORTING : execution_audit_record(operator, directive)
REPORTING --> CLI : execution_audit_record\nadapter/action/execution_status/reason_code/command

CONTEXT --> CONTRACTS : adjacent surfaces\nand trust invariants
CONTEXT --> ADMISSIBILITY : proposal-only semantic context\nand ontology vocabulary

note right of SECURITY
Decision reasons fed into routing:
- unknown_action
- proposal_from_public_source
- requires_confirmation
- resource_scope_uri_forbidden
- resource_scope_out_of_bounds
- secret_material_detected
end note

note right of ADMISSIBILITY
Transform surfaces evaluated before READY:
- F_cap
- F_channel
- F_delta
- F_onto
- ZOS proposal-only bridge
- multi-step attack-chain replay
end note

note right of PRECONDITION
These checks are hard gates before READY:
- deny => blocked
- requires_confirmation => operator review
- allow + preconditions pass => ready
end note

@enduml
